{
  "texts": [
    "For all methods, features can be calculated for single image tiles, a single slide, or image tiles read from TFRecords.Several pretrained networks can be used for converting images into feature vectors.",
    "Slideflow includes an API for calculating layer activations at any arbitrary neural network layer for models pretrained on ImageNet, by specifying an architecture name and layer name.",
    "If multiple layers are specified, activations at each layer will be calculated and concatenated.",
    "An API is also included for easily generating features using the pretrained, pathology-specific CTransPath [50] and RetCCL [51] networks.",
    "Finetuned classifiers trained with Slideflow can also be used for feature generation, calculating activations at any arbitrary neural network layer."
  ]
}